create a ec2 instance in aws with 4cpus and 100GiB 
---->install docker
--->Install docker and create a directory "mkdir argocd && cd argocd"
--->type this command "wget https://github.com/argoproj/argo-cd/archive/refs/tags/v2.7.2.tar.gz"
--->type this command "tar -zxvf v2.7.2.tar.gz"
-->type this command "ls -ltrh"
--->type this command "cd argocd-cd-v2.7.2/"
--->type this command "ls -ltrh"
--->Type this command "docker build -t argoproj/argocd:v2.7.2_v3 ."
--->enter "docker images"
--->Type "docker login"( this will ask for username and pwd and you will be successfully logged in
--->Type "docker tag argocd:v2.7.2_v3 pavanicherla/argocd:v2.7.2_v3"(This command will push utilityapp:v2.0.1-f into my account by creating a repository with same name)
13)Type docker images (this command checks whether the  pavanicherla/argocd:v2.7.2_v3 is in the docker images or not
14)Type docker push  pavanicherla/argocd:v2.7.2_v3( this will push docker image to docker hub in your account)
